                                Repurposing old furniture is not only an eco-friendly way to refresh your home, but it also allows you to get creative and save money. Whether it’s an old dresser, a worn-out chair, or a discarded table, you can give new life to almost any piece of furniture. With just a little time and effort, you can turn outdated or unused furniture into stylish, functional items that perfectly fit your space.
                            </p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Start with Simple Sanding and Painting</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">One of the easiest and most effective ways to repurpose old furniture is by sanding and painting. A fresh coat of paint can completely change the look of a piece and make it blend seamlessly with your home’s style.</p>
                            
