                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Repurpose an Old Dresser into a Bathroom Vanity</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">An old dresser can easily be transformed into a bathroom vanity with a few modifications. This project adds charm and storage to your bathroom while giving the dresser a second life.</p>
                            
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You'll need to cut a hole in the top for the sink and adjust internal drawers to accommodate plumbing.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Turn an Old Door into a Coffee Table</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If you have an old door, consider repurposing it into a coffee table. It is a great way to add a rustic or industrial touch to your living room.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Reupholster Chairs for a Fresh Look</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Reupholstering is an excellent way to give a chair a completely new look. You can choose from a variety of fabrics to suit your taste.</p>
                            
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Transform a Wooden Pallet into a Bed Frame</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Pallets are sturdy and can be easily stacked and modified to create a rustic, low-cost bed frame. Ensure you sand them thoroughly to avoid splinters.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Create a Bookshelf from Wooden Crates</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Wooden crates can be stacked vertically or horizontally to create modular bookshelves. This adds character and flexible storage to any room.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Repurpose an Old Ladder into a Shelf or Towel Rack</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">An old wooden ladder is perfect for a farmhouse touch. Lean it against a wall and use the rungs for towels or attach small boards to create shelving steps.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Create a Wall Organizer from Old Drawers</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Mount old drawers directly to the wall. They act as shadow boxes for decor or deep shelves for entryways and offices.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Refinish an Old Coffee Table</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If the structure is good but the surface is scratched, refinishing with a modern wood stain or bold paint color can restore it to a like-new condition.</p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">FAQs</h2>
